    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Rear Bumper Assembly</title>
        <para>The rear bumper assembly is a full wrap around style bumper bolted to the chassis frame assembly. The
            optional tow hooks are also mounted to the frame assembly and are located below the bumper assembly (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f4700640">Fig. 40, Item 4</hotlnk>) at the rear of the bus.
        </para>
        <figure id="f4700640" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg47/g4700640.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="288px"
                     scalefitheight="288px"/>
            <caption>Figure 40. Rear Bumper Assembly and Tow Hooks</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. D.O.T. RED REFLECTOR</callout1>
                <callout1>2. BODY SIDE RUB RAIL</callout1>
                <callout1>3. EXHAUST PIPE</callout1>
                <callout1>4. REAR TOW HOOKS</callout1>
                <callout1>5. BUMPER ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                <callout1>6. REAR BUMPER TRANSITION PANELS</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
    </svcsubproc>
